# Atlassian Chat Agent — credentials for the Rovo MCP server.
# Copy to `.env` and fill in. `.env` is git-ignored; never commit real tokens.
# The runners (prober.py / chat.py) auto-load this file.

# --- Auth header for the agent (agent.yaml: auth.headers Authorization) ---
# agent.yaml sends `Authorization: ${ATLASSIAN_AUTH_HEADER}` to the Rovo MCP
# server, so set the FULL header value here.
#
# Personal API token (must be a SCOPED token created via the MCP flow:
#   https://id.atlassian.com/manage-profile/security/api-tokens?appId=mcp&selectedScopes=all )
# -> Basic base64(email:token). Generate it with:
#   export ATLASSIAN_EMAIL="your.email@example.com"
#   export ATLASSIAN_API_TOKEN="your_scoped_api_token"
#   ATLASSIAN_AUTH_HEADER="Basic $(printf '%s' "$ATLASSIAN_EMAIL:$ATLASSIAN_API_TOKEN" | base64)"
#
# Service-account API key -> Bearer (Rovo rejects personal tokens as Bearer):
#   ATLASSIAN_AUTH_HEADER="Bearer your_service_account_api_key"
ATLASSIAN_AUTH_HEADER="Basic your_base64_email_colon_token"

# --- Demo seeding only (demo/seed_demo.py) ---
# The seeder builds Basic auth itself from the email + token below, and derives
# the cloud id from the site URL.
ATLASSIAN_EMAIL="your.email@example.com"
ATLASSIAN_API_TOKEN="your_scoped_api_token"
ATLASSIAN_SITE="https://your-site.atlassian.net"
# Optional: set the cloud id explicitly instead of deriving it from the site.
# ATLASSIAN_CLOUD_ID="00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"

# --- Interactions API (Data Plane) ---
# Optional: overrides the ADC-resolved project.
# GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT="your-gcp-project-id"
